				<h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mb-8">Private Image Tools For Everyday Work</h2>
				<p><strong>Image Tool Stack</strong> is a collection of free online image tools for common jobs like converting PNG to JPG, compressing images, resizing photos, cropping pictures, removing metadata, and creating PDFs from images. The tools run in your browser, so your files stay on your device instead of being uploaded to a server.</p>

				<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mt-12 mb-4">Convert Images Without Uploading</h3>
				<p>Use the image converter tools when you need a quick format change for web, email, social media, or client delivery. You can convert between popular formats like PNG, JPG, JPEG, WebP, HEIC, SVG, AVIF, TIFF, BMP, and PDF. Each converter is designed around one clear task, which makes pages like PNG to JPG, HEIC to JPG, WebP to PNG, and SVG to PNG easier to find and faster to use.</p>

				<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mt-12 mb-4">Compress, Resize, And Crop Images</h3>
				<p>Large images can slow down websites, emails, and uploads. The image compressor helps reduce file size, while the image resizer changes dimensions for websites, marketplaces, documents, and social platforms. The cropper and aspect-ratio tools help prepare clean images for thumbnails, banners, profile photos, product listings, and posts.</p>

				<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mt-12 mb-4">Useful Tools For Designers, Marketers, And Creators</h3>
				<p>Beyond conversion and compression, Image Tool Stack includes practical utilities such as a color picker, palette generator, EXIF metadata viewer, background remover, watermark tool, PDF tools, QR tools, filters, and social media resizers. These pages target real tasks people search for, while keeping the workflow simple: choose a tool, process locally, and download the result.</p>

				<h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink mt-12 mb-4">Built Around Privacy</h3>
				<p>Most online image tools require file uploads. Image Tool Stack is different: the core processing happens locally in the browser whenever the tool supports it. That makes it useful for personal photos, client assets, screenshots, documents, product images, and other files you would rather not send elsewhere.</p>
